# CEO (Build) review — Sanctuary Worship Playback Engine

## Verified (ran tools, did not assume)
- `vite build` recompiles clean: 25 modules, 0 errors, output hashes (index-DyWHdn_i.js / index-CZdTz6sh.css) identical to what is deployed.
- Deployed dir `michaelwegter.com/public/demos/audio-software-engineer-needed-for/` has index.html + assets/ + favicon + icons; base paths absolute and correct (`/demos/.../assets/...`).
- Registry entry present in `workSamples.js` (id 12, slug, category Music, status live, href via BASE_URL, client/postingSummary/builtFor/date filled). Portfolio chrome, not demo styling — correct.
- JS/CSS bundles: 0 em/en dashes (all user-visible runtime text clean).

## Feature richness vs target (10/10)
Strong match. Posting's eight pain points map 1:1 to working features:
- transport reliability -> Transport (play/pause/stop, pauseOffset resume)
- section navigation -> SectionNav clickable chips
- audio sync / click timing -> Chris Wilson 25/100ms lookahead Scheduler, sample-accurate loop seek
- guide cue timing -> Scheduler cue dispatch + slide-in cue cards
- stem routing -> 6-stem signal chain (gain->pan->mute->master)
- mixer channel behavior -> 6 ChannelStrips (fader/pan/mute/solo with correct solo interaction)
- count-in -> offline-rendered click + 4-3-2-1-GO overlay
- engine stability -> OfflineAudioContext synthesis, AudioContext gesture-resume handling
Plus 3 full songs, A/B loop, waveform scrubber w/ click-to-seek, keyboard shortcuts. Genuinely full-featured; no REDIRECT needed — plan and research foundation were sufficient.

